</svg></span>Method<div class="wprm-decoration-line" style="border-color: var(--glacier-header-text);border-width: 2px;"></div><div class="wprm-header-toggle"><a role="button" aria-expanded="false" class="wprm-expandable-button wprm-expandable-button-show" style="color: var(--glacier-header-text)" aria-label="Show Section"><span class="wprm-recipe-icon wprm-collapsible-icon"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 16 16"><g class="nc-icon-wrapper" stroke-width="1" fill="none" stroke="var(--glacier-header-text)" stroke-miterlimit="10" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><polyline points="3.5,9.5 8,5 12.5,9.5 "></polyline></g></svg></span> </a><a role="button" aria-expanded="true" class="wprm-expandable-button wprm-expandable-button-hide" style="color: var(--glacier-header-text)" aria-label="Hide Section"><span class="wprm-recipe-icon wprm-collapsible-icon"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 16 16"><g class="nc-icon-wrapper" stroke-width="1" fill="none" stroke="var(--glacier-header-text)" stroke-miterlimit="10" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><polyline points="3.5,6.5 8,11 12.5,6.5 "></polyline></g></svg></span> </a></div></h3><div class="wprm-internal-container wprm-internal-container-instructions" style="background-color: var(--glacier-background);"><div class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><ol class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-18195-step-0-0" class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;margin-left: 20px;" value="1"><div class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 10px;"><span style="display: block;">Bring a large pot of salted water to a boil. Add the penne pasta and cook according to package directions until al dente. Drain the pasta and set it aside.</span></div></li><li id="wprm-recipe-18195-step-0-1" class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;margin-left: 20px;" value="2"><div class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 10px;"><span style="display: block;">While the pasta cooks, chop the bacon into small pieces. Cook the bacon in a large skillet over medium heat until crispy, about 5-7 minutes. Remove the bacon with a slotted spoon and drain on paper towels, leaving the bacon drippings in the skillet.</span></div></li><li id="wprm-recipe-18195-step-0-2" class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;margin-left: 20px;" value="3"><div class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 10px;"><span style="display: block;">Add the butter to the skillet with the bacon drippings. Once melted, add the chicken pieces in a single layer. Season with garlic powder, onion powder, salt, and pepper. Cook for 5-7 minutes, stirring occasionally, until the chicken is cooked through and no longer pink inside.</span></div></li><li id="wprm-recipe-18195-step-0-3" class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;margin-left: 20px;" value="4"><div class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 10px;"><span style="display: block;">Sprinkle the flour over the chicken and stir to coat. Cook for 1 minute to remove the raw flour taste. Gradually pour in the milk while stirring constantly to create a smooth sauce.</span></div></li><li id="wprm-recipe-18195-step-0-4" class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;margin-left: 20px;" value="5"><div class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 10px;"><span style="display: block;">Stir in the ranch dressing and shredded cheddar cheese. Continue cooking and stirring until the cheese is melted and the sauce has thickened slightly, about 2-3 minutes.</span></div></li><li id="wprm-recipe-18195-step-0-5" class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;margin-left: 20px;" value="6"><div class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 10px;"><span style="display: block;">Add the cooked pasta and crispy bacon to the skillet. Gently toss everything together until the pasta is evenly coated in the sauce. Cook for another minute until heated through.</span></div></li><li id="wprm-recipe-18195-step-0-6" class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;margin-left: 20px;" value="7"><div class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 10px;"><span style="display: block;">Remove from heat and garnish with chopped fresh parsley before serving.</span></div></li></ol></div></div></div><div id="recipe-video"></div><div id="recipe-18195-notes" class="wprm-recipe-notes-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3 class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-notes-header wprm-block-text-bold wprm-align-left wprm-header-decoration-icon-line wprm-expandable-container-separated wprm-expandable-expanded" style="padding: 10px 20px;background-color: var(--glacier-header-background);"><span class="wprm-recipe-icon" aria-hidden="true"><svg width="28" height="28" viewBox="0 0 28 28" fill="none" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
